{
  "texts": [
    "Both features are aggregated and form new feature vectors by updating the values to include the new message.",
    "(4.1)h (k+1) u = UPDATE (k) h (k) u, AGGREGATE (k) h (k) v, ∀ v ∈ N (u) (4.2) = UPDATE (k) h (k) u, m (k) N (u)Fig. 6 How a single node aggregates messages from its adjacent neighbor nodes Fig.",
    "7 Message passing mechanism in GNN Equations 4.1 and 4.2 shows that h denotes the message, u represents the node number, and k indicates the iteration number.",
    "Where AGGREGATE and UPDATE are arbitrarily differentiable functions (i.e., neural networks), and mN(u) is the \"message, \" which is aggregated from u's graph neighborhood N(u).",
    "We employ superscripts to identify the embeddings and functions at various message-passing iterations."
  ]
}